Detroit police are working to find two people wanted in connection with a fatal hit-and-run this week on the city’s west side.
Detroit police said a woman lost control of the Dodge Journey she was driving, striking the 83-year-old (Photo: Detroit Police Department)The man, whose name was not released, died.
Detroit police on Wednesday night released a photo of the woman they described as a suspect.
A description of the man who drove the Chevy was not available, police said.
Anyone who has information is asked to call the Detroit Police Department’s Fatal Squad at (313) 596-2260.